10/07/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Serbian Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic said on Wednesday (July 9th) that Belgrade appreciates Montenegro's "reserved" stance on recognising Kosovo's unilaterally declared independence. Jeremic expressed Belgrade's gratitude after meeting with Montenegrin Foreign Minister Milan Rocen, President Filip Vujanovic, Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic and Parliamentary Speaker Ranko Krivokapic in Podgorica. (Politika - 10/07/08; RTCG, Makfax, Fonet, Tanjug, B92 - 09/07/08)
